oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Rear wing door of Cragfont
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Exterior view of rear wing door detail at Cragfont. The door has six flush panels arranged in three tiers and a window above it. The screen door is propped open by a rock. Some of the hardware on the door has been removed. The wooden porch is also visible.

The late Georgian style home was built between 1798 and 1802, and was originally home of General James Winchester. It was named after the Rocky Bluff it is located on. Cragfont was occupied by the Winchester family until 1864.
